column11:
  We establish the comparison principle, existence and regularity of viscosity
solutions to the following problem concerning the mixed operator:
  \begin{align}
  \begin{cases}
  \alpha\mathcal{M}^+_{\lambda,\Lambda}\big(D^2_{\mathbbm{H}^N,S}u\big)-\beta\big(-\Delta_{\mathbbm{H}^N}\big)^su=f
&\text{in } \,{\Omega},
  u=g &\text{in } \,\mathbbm{H}^N\setminus\Omega,
  \end{cases}
  \end{align}
  where $\mathcal{M}_{\lambda,\Lambda}^+$ is the extremal Pucci's operator and
$(-\Delta_{\mathbbm{H}^N})^s$ denotes the fractional sub-Laplacian on
Heisenberg group. Here $\alpha\geq 0$ and $\beta>0$ are constants.
